Minister of Basic Education Angie Motshekga will brief the media to provide an update on the readiness for the reopening of schools. JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga is briefing the nation on Monday morning. Motshekga was set to address the country on the department's readiness to reopen schools on Sunday, but the briefing was postponed. READ: Alert level 3: Reopening of schools delayed Previously she announced that Grade 7 and 12 pupils will start on Monday. Government, however, made an eleventh-hour about-turn on the reopening of schools. READ: Basic Education Minister's briefing on reopening of schools postponed It said the Grade 7s and matrics will only return to school on 8 June. Some teachers unions, students and pupils associations say schools are not ready to accept pupils. READ: SAHRC takes Western Cape to court over reopening of schools Schools have been closed for two months. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.